Turkey Stocks: Koza Altin, Logo Yazilim, Sabanci Holding Move

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-11-29T16:09:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-29/turkey-stocks-koza-altin-logo-yazilim-sabanci-holding-move.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  fell for the first day in three, losing 0.4 percent to
52,092.78 at the close in Istanbul.  The following stocks were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Haci Omer Sabanci Holding AS (SAHOL)  , Turkey’s second-
biggest group of companies, increased 0.7 percent to 5.54 liras,
rising for a third day. The company plans to set up a 3.5
billion lira ($1.9 billion) jointly owned unit with Austria’s
 Verbund AG (VER)  to run all of the partners’ energy ventures in
Turkey.  Koza Altin Isletmeleri AS (KOZAL)  , a gold miner, added
5.5 percent to 26.70 liras after saying environmental challenges
to its mine at Ovacik had been rejected in court.  Logo Yazilim Sanayi & Ticaret AS (LOGO)  , a software
company, gained 1.2 percent to 1.67 liras after saying its
purchase of Coretech Bilgi Teknolojisi Hizmetleri AS, which
develops business management systems, had been completed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
